SOCCER 10 POOL OF THE DAYMonday 20 June S10 V1 Sao Paulo and Palmeiras meet tonight in what is always a fierce derby in Brazilian soccer, with Palmeiras sitting at the top of the league table. More details at www.soccer6.co.za. M1 Fredrikstad vs Raufoss: Fredrikstad have lost their last three outings in the Norwegian second division. Raufoss are one point behind them in the standings.M2 Fram Reykjavik vs IB Vestmannaeyja: IBV lead Fram 19-9 in the win count of past clashes between these two clubs from Iceland. There have also been 13 draws.M3 Breidablik UBK vs KA Akreyri: Breidablik are unbeaten in their past nine clashes with KA winning the last three.M4 UMF Stjarnan vs KR Reykjavik: Stjarnan hosted KR in the cup late last month and lost 3-0. Now they play them in the league where Stjarnan have a two point lead over KR.M5 Godoy Cruz vs Defensa y Justicia: Godoy Cruz beat Defensa y Justicia 2-1 in their last clash to end a run of seven games without success against them.M6 Gimnasia La Plata vs Racing Club: Both of the last two meetings between these Argentine sides have ended in goalless draws.M7 Velez Sarsfield vs Rosario Central: Rosario have beaten Velez 1-0 in each of their past two meetings but both games were at home.M8 Sao Paulo vs Palmeiras: Derby match in the league follows three clashes in the Paulista state championship earlier this year with two wins for Palmeiras and one for Sao Paulo.M9 Independiente vs Estudiantes: Independiente are without a victory in their past four home games against Estudiantes.M10 Newell’s Old Boys vs Argentinos Juniors: Argentinos Juniors have on their past three games against Newell’s but all were at home. Suggested permutation: R16.00 1 x 1 x 1 x 3 x 1 x 3 x 1 x 1,2 x 1,2 x 1,2